220
00:13:57,904 --> 00:13:59,906
♪ Them in school yet ♪

221
00:14:51,457 --> 00:14:54,459
I wish it was
tomorrow morning.

222
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:56,621
Kolya says we'll go to the
theater when we get to Kiev.

223
00:14:56,963 --> 00:14:59,466
All we have to do is
apply for the tickets.

224
00:14:59,467 --> 00:15:00,966
We'll have three
whole days in Kiev.

225
00:15:00,967 --> 00:15:02,968
We shall see everything.

226
00:15:02,969 --> 00:15:04,970
It's been a good year.

227
00:15:04,971 --> 00:15:08,475
Scholarship to the university,
of course, means the most.

228
00:15:08,476 --> 00:15:10,976
There was a medal
for marksmanship.

229
00:15:10,977 --> 00:15:12,979
And now this vacation.

230
00:15:14,981 --> 00:15:16,982
We'll be separated for a year.

231
00:15:16,983 --> 00:15:19,985
You'll be getting a scholarship
the following year.

232
00:15:19,986 --> 00:15:22,489
But it's this year
I'm thinking about.

233
00:15:22,490 --> 00:15:23,990
That's a long time.

234
00:15:25,491 --> 00:15:27,993
I don't think it
is at our age.

235
00:15:27,994 --> 00:15:29,494
You don't think so?

236
00:15:29,495 --> 00:15:31,497
How strange.

237
00:15:31,998 --> 00:15:33,999
What are you saying, Marina?

238
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:37,504
Nothing. I don't want
to talk about it.

239
00:15:39,505 --> 00:15:44,509
It's odd you don't think a year
away from me is a long time.

240
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:46,511
It doesn't worry you?

241
00:15:46,512 --> 00:15:48,513
No.

242
00:15:48,514 --> 00:15:50,015
All right.

243
00:15:50,016 --> 00:15:53,019
You don't have to keep
saying it over and over.

244
00:15:54,020 --> 00:15:57,023
Are you sure you feel
about me as you used to?

245
00:15:58,024 --> 00:16:00,527
I don't like this talk.
It -- it's bad.

246
00:16:00,528 --> 00:16:03,029
It's only natural that I --
it's not natural at all.

247
00:16:03,529 --> 00:16:05,031
It's not like you.

248
00:16:05,531 --> 00:16:08,533
I've loved you since I was
old enough to see you.

249
00:16:08,534 --> 00:16:11,036
I will love you until I die.

250
00:16:11,037 --> 00:16:12,537
That's the way it is,

251
00:16:12,538 --> 00:16:14,040
and there's no need
to talk about it.

252
00:16:14,540 --> 00:16:16,041
You mean you'll never
talk about it?

253
00:16:16,042 --> 00:16:17,542
You'll never tell me?

254
00:16:17,543 --> 00:16:20,045
I'll tell you in my own time.

255
00:16:20,046 --> 00:16:22,549
But I'll not tell
you to waste time.

256
00:16:23,049 --> 00:16:24,050
Look here, Marina.

257
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:27,052
